# Angular Button Component

Use `app-button` (AppButtonComponent) instead of `p-button` (PrimeNG Button) directly.

## Why

- Consistent API and patterns across the app
- Single place to enforce accessibility (e.g. ariaLabel for icon-only)
- Easier to change global button styling or behavior
- Avoids divergent patterns (e.g. different severity names, missing loading states)

## Import

```ts
import { AppButtonComponent } from '../shared/components/app-button/app-button.component';
// or from your feature path, e.g.:
// import { AppButtonComponent } from '../../../../shared/components/app-button/app-button.component';
```

## Usage

```ts
// Primary button with click
<app-button label="Save" (clicked)="onSave()" />

// Secondary, loading state
<app-button label="Submit" type="submit" severity="secondary" [loading]="loading()" />

// Router link
<app-button label="Go to Docs" [routerLink]="['/docs']" />

// Icon-only (provide ariaLabel)
<app-button icon="pi pi-times" severity="secondary" ariaLabel="Close" (clicked)="close()" />

// Danger variant
<app-button label="Delete" severity="danger" (clicked)="onDelete()" />
```

## API

| Input       | Type                         | Default     |
| ----------- | ---------------------------- | ----------- |
| label       | string                       | ''          |
| severity    | primary \| secondary \| ...  | 'primary'   |
| type        | 'button' \| 'submit' \| 'reset' | 'button' |
| loading     | boolean                      | false       |
| disabled    | boolean                      | false       |
| icon        | string (e.g. 'pi pi-check')  | undefined   |
| iconPos     | 'left' \| 'right' \| ...     | 'left'      |
| routerLink  | string \| string[]           | undefined   |
| styleClass  | string                       | ''          |
| ariaLabel   | string                       | undefined   |
| fluid       | boolean                      | false       |

| Output  | Type  |
| ------- | ----- |
| clicked | Event |
